Northam Offers 5.9% Wage Hike; Talks to Resume Oct. 13

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-09-28T10:35:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/northam-offers-5-9-wage-hike-talks-to-resume-oct-13-correct-.html
(Corrects date in headline, second paragraph.)  Northam Platinum Ltd. (NHM) , the South
African producer that had a 43-day wage strike last year,
offered workers a 5.9 percent pay increase yesterday, a  National
Union of Mineworkers  negotiator said.  The union is demanding 15 percent, Zwelitsha Tantsi said by
mobile phone today. Talks will continue on Oct. 13, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carli Lourens at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net  